► **THINKING**

Let me understand the VLQ encoding/decoding requirements:

1. **Encoding**: Convert 32-bit unsigned integers to variable-length quantities
   - Each byte uses 7 bits for data, 1 bit (bit 7) as continuation flag
   - If more bytes follow, set bit 7 (0x80)
   - Last byte has bit 7 clear
   - Examples:
     - 0-127 → 1 byte (no continuation bit)
     - 128-16383 → 2 bytes
     - etc.

2. **Decoding**: Convert variable-length quantities back to integers
   - Read bytes until one with bit 7 clear
   - Each byte contributes 7 bits to the result
   - Need to handle errors (incomplete sequences, overflow)

Let me implement this in Java:

For encoding:
- Process each number
- Extract 7-bit chunks from least significant to most significant
- Set continuation bit on all but the last chunk
- Reverse the order since we extract LSB first

For decoding:
- Read bytes sequentially
- Extract 7 bits from each byte (clear bit 7)
- Combine them into a 32-bit integer
- Check for incomplete sequences or overflow

Let me write the code:

```java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

class VariableLengthQuantity {
    
    List<String> encode(List<Long> numbers) {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        
        for (Long number : numbers) {
            if (number == null || number < 0 || number > 0xFFFFFFFFL) {
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("Number out of range");
            }
            
            List<String> bytes = encodeNumber(number);
            result.addAll(bytes);
        }
        
        return result;
    }
    
    private List<String> encodeNumber(Long number) {
        List<String> bytes = new ArrayList<>();
        
        if (number == 0) {
            bytes.add("0x00");
            return bytes;
        }
        
        // Extract 7-bit chunks from LSB to MSB
        List<Integer> chunks = new ArrayList<>();
        long n = number;
        
        while (n > 0) {
            chunks.add((int)(n & 0x7F));
            n >>= 7;
        }
        
        // Reverse to get MSB first
        for (int i = chunks.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            int chunk = chunks.get(i);
            if (i > 0) {
                // Set continuation bit for all but last byte
                chunk |= 0x80;
            }
            bytes.add(String.format("0x%02X", chunk));
        }
        
        return bytes;
    }
    
    List<String> decode(List<Long> bytes) {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        long currentNumber = 0;
        boolean hasContinuation = false;
        
        for (Long byteVal : bytes) {
            if (byteVal == null || byteVal < 0 || byteVal > 0xFFL) {
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("Byte out of range");
            }
            
            int b = byteVal.intValue();
            int value = b & 0x7F;
            currentNumber = (currentNumber << 7) | value;
            
            if ((b & 0x80) == 0) {
                // Last byte of sequence
                result.add(String.format("0x%08X", currentNumber));
                currentNumber = 0;
                hasContinuation = false;
            } else {
                hasContinuation = true;
            }
        }
        
        if (hasContinuation) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Incomplete sequence");
        }
        
        return result;
    }
}
```

